text: Kahang in Kulang District Kahang is a mukim in Kluang District, Johor, Malaysia. It is particularly known as the final stop before heading to the Endau Rompin National Park and located along the Malaysia Federal Route 50.http://www.nst.com.my/news/2015/11/113875/inclusive-and-sustainable?d=1 ==Geography== The mukim spans over an area of 548 km2.http://jpbd.johor.gov.my/images/jpbd_DokumenTerbitan/Handbook.pdf ==Economy== Kahang has an organic paddy farm 28 miles away from Kluang. ==School in Kahang== ===Primary school=== * Sekolah Kebangsaan Seri Sedohok * Sekolah Kebangsaan Ladang Mutiara * Sekolah Kebangsaan Kahang * Sekolah Jenis Kebangsaan (Tamil) Kahang Batu 24 * Sekolah Jenis Kebangsaan (Cina) Kahang ===Secondary school=== * Sekolah Menengah Kebangsaan Kahang ==References== Category:Kluang District Category:Mukims of Johor
